50|$|Verse 9 {{refers to}} a dispute between Michael the Archangel and the devil about the body of Moses. Some interpreters {{understand}} this reference to be an allusion to the events described in Zechariah 3:1-2. The classical theologian Origen attributes this reference to the non-canonical Assumption of Moses. According to <b>James</b> <b>Charlesworth,</b> {{there is no evidence}} the surviving book of this name ever contained any such content. Others believe it to be in the lost ending of the book.|$|E
